-- Brazil’s Corinthians Beat Al-Ahly in Club World Cup Semifinals
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-12-12T13:30:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-12/brazil-s-corinthians-beat-al-ahly-in-club-world-cup-semifinals.html
Brazilian club Corinthians defeated
Egypt’s Al-Ahly 1-0 in the semifinals of soccer’s Club  World Cup 
in Japan.  Paolo Guerrero scored in the 30th minute in Toyota to send
Corinthians to the Dec. 16 final against European titleholder
Chelsea or Mexican club Monterrey. The South American champion
won the initial Club World Cup in 2000.  Earlier today, Sanfrecce Hiroshima of Japan beat Asian
champion Ulsan Hyundai of South Korea 3-2 in the fifth-place
match. Hisato Sato scored two goals for the Japanese J-League
winner and Satoru Yamagishi added one.  Chelsea is aiming to give Europe a sixth straight title at
the annual competition, which is contested by the champions of
each continent’s soccer federation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 